column2: Samples analyzed at Madison-Dane County Health Department Lab.
Samples analyzed at Madison-Dane County Health Department Lab.
Water is 9.0 feet deep.  Partly cloudy- southerly breeze- saw 6 turtles- some small fish- slight flow of water Rice Lake into Sweet Lake.
Water is 9.25 feet deep.  Clear- calm- slight southerly breeze- 4 turtles on west bank.
Water is 9.25 feet deep.  Partly cloudy- southerly breeze- saw 2 Great Blue Herons- 8 turtles on west bank.
Water is 9.5 feet deep and was able to paddle and pole from Sweet Lake to Rice Lake without portage.
Easy to launch with 11 feet- 2 inches depth at deep hole.  Several cars in lot- canoes- row boats- fishermen- windy with pat sun.
Parking lot about half flooded with water depth of 11 feet- 6 inches at deep hole.  Sunny- slight breeze- saw eagle- osprey- heron- hawk.
Parking lot still partially flooded- with water depth 11.5 feet at deep hole.  sunny- sleigh breeze.
Parking lot still flooded with water depth 12.0 feet at deep hole.  Partly cloudy- calm- good depth readings.
Parking lot still flooded with 12.0 feet water depth at deep hole.  One other kayaker in lake- calm- sunny- particles of algae- not strings like in Koshkonong.
